those boundary
conditions become natural

00:17:47.220 --> 00:17:52.640
if you think those
places in spacetime

00:17:52.640 --> 00:17:57.380
are special places which
something can happen.

00:17:57.380 --> 00:18:00.710
It's not the same
as other places.

00:18:00.710 --> 00:18:05.390
And to say those
[INAUDIBLE] give a name.

00:18:05.390 --> 00:18:11.250
So you imagine--
so for example, you

00:18:11.250 --> 00:18:36.600
can imagine some spacetime
defect sitting at, say,

00:18:36.600 --> 00:18:46.425
this xp plus 1, x equal to
a, sitting at that location.

00:18:50.690 --> 00:18:52.170
So where open string can end.

00:19:03.920 --> 00:19:06.590
So such a defect,
we'll call it D-brane.

00:19:11.895 --> 00:19:12.520
We give a name.

00:19:23.360 --> 00:19:25.730
So D is clear because
it's Dirichlet boundary

00:19:25.730 --> 00:19:28.820
condition, and the brane because
it's some extended surface.

00:19:28.820 --> 00:19:29.320
OK?

00:19:35.110 --> 00:19:39.080
And so we often use a
notation to say Dp-brane.

00:19:42.790 --> 00:19:46.550
So p denotes the [INAUDIBLE]
spatial dimensions

00:19:46.550 --> 00:19:47.750
along the brane.

00:19:47.750 --> 00:19:48.580
OK?

00:19:48.580 --> 00:19:51.490
So in this case, there's
p spatial dimensions

00:19:51.490 --> 00:20:00.360
along the plane-- along this
brane, so we call it Dp-brane.

00:20:00.360 --> 00:20:00.860
OK?

00:20:09.110 --> 00:20:17.330
So right now, Dp-brane
is merely just a place

00:20:17.330 --> 00:20:19.620
which impose a boundary
conditions which

00:20:19.620 --> 00:20:24.750
open strings can end.

00:20:24.750 --> 00:20:28.610
But we will soon see
that actually a Dp-brane

00:20:28.610 --> 00:20:32.900
is a dynamic object, and it's
actually a dynamic object.

00:20:32.900 --> 00:20:36.770
And this actually can move,
can fluctuate, can jump around,

00:20:36.770 --> 00:20:37.730
et cetera.

00:20:37.730 --> 00:20:39.790
OK?

00:20:39.790 --> 00:20:44.070
And so also from
this perspective,

00:20:44.070 --> 00:20:46.295
our previous Neumann
boundary condition,

00:20:46.295 --> 00:20:50.950
if we have Neumann
in all direction,

00:20:50.950 --> 00:20:59.060
so if we have Neumann boundary
condition in all directions,

00:20:59.060 --> 00:21:03.925
then in this case the open
string can end everywhere.

00:21:10.229 --> 00:21:10.770
End anywhere.

00:21:18.250 --> 00:21:27.690
From this new perspective, we
call this space-filling brane.

00:21:27.690 --> 00:21:30.620
We call this actually
a space-filling brane.

00:21:34.241 --> 00:21:34.740
OK?

00:21:37.950 --> 00:21:40.610
So the Dirichlet boundary--
the Neumann boundary condition

00:21:40.610 --> 00:21:43.530
