00:33:56.647 --> 00:33:57.480
So important remark.

00:34:04.580 --> 00:34:12.760
So a Dp-brane, as
we said before,

00:34:12.760 --> 00:34:14.190
it breaks translation symmetry.

00:34:27.010 --> 00:34:29.239
Translation and the
Lorentz symmetries.

00:34:40.032 --> 00:34:40.532
OK?

00:34:45.750 --> 00:34:54.570
Of the original Minkowski
spacetime to your sub-group.

00:34:54.570 --> 00:34:58.630
So the subgroup is
that you have-- still

00:34:58.630 --> 00:35:01.700
have translational symmetry
and the Lorentz symmetry

00:35:01.700 --> 00:35:03.980
along the brane direction.

00:35:03.980 --> 00:35:06.080
So along the brane
direction, you still

00:35:06.080 --> 00:35:08.330
can translate-- your
string can still

00:35:08.330 --> 00:35:09.990
translate in that direction.

00:35:09.990 --> 00:35:13.350
And there's still Lorentz
symmetry in that direction.

00:35:13.350 --> 00:35:18.000
So there's still Poincare
symmetry in 1,p-- 1 comma p--

00:35:18.000 --> 00:35:22.620
so in the time and the p spatial
dimensions along the brane.

00:35:22.620 --> 00:35:25.890
And then you have rotational
symmetries in the direction

00:35:25.890 --> 00:35:27.570
transverse to the brane.

00:35:27.570 --> 00:35:31.120
So that's D minus 1 minus p.

00:35:31.120 --> 00:35:36.550
So that's the rotation
among those coordinates.

00:35:36.550 --> 00:35:38.050
So you can have the
Lorentz symmetry

00:35:38.050 --> 00:35:40.660
along those directions,
then the rotational symmetry

00:35:40.660 --> 00:35:41.751
is along those directions.

00:35:41.751 --> 00:35:42.250
OK?

00:35:42.250 --> 00:35:43.920
So this is for Dp-brane.

00:35:43.920 --> 00:35:47.495
So this is the
remaining symmetry.

00:35:50.390 --> 00:35:54.590
So this is remaining
symmetry say if you have

00:35:54.590 --> 00:35:58.275
a Dp-brane in the spacetime.

00:35:58.275 --> 00:36:01.850
Of course, if you have
multiple Dp-brane, et cetera,

